Description: A hunk of verdant metal torn from the Emerald Weapon.
Name: Emerald Plating

Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the Emerald Weapon.
Name: Emerald Barding

Description: A suit of chocobo armor modeled after that worn by a legendary queen's personal guard─willingly and otherwise.
Name: Queen's Guard Barding

Description: A suit of chocobo armor as worn by those legendary birds said to carry gifts from the stars. In fact, it was borrowed directly from one of the aforementioned legendary birds, making it as authentic as it can possibly be.
Name: Authentic Starlight Barding

Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to best conceal Eastern foodstuffs about one's person in the likely event the hors d'oeuvres on offer are insufficient to sate one's hunger. Use to learn the /riceball emote.
Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Concealing Meals

Singular: copy of Ballroom Etiquette - Apples with Aplomb
Plural: copies of Ballroom Etiquette - Apples with Aplomb
Description: An illustrated manual of how to enjoy a delicious apple while projecting an air of unassailable dignity in spite of your squirrel-like gnawing. Use to learn the /eatapple emote.
Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Apples with Aplomb

Singular: copy of Ballroom Etiquette - Good Will Seeking
Plural: copies of Ballroom Etiquette - Good Will Seeking
Description: An illustrated manual of how to bring oneself into the good graces of others. Use to learn the /wringhands emote.
Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Good Will Seeking

Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to operate the quaint device known as a “broom” in event of dire circumstances involving the absence of one's servants. Use to learn the /broom emote.
Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Next, Godliness

Description: An illustrated manual explaining the ideal method for painting over pesky or potentially haunted patterns in one's wallpaper. Use to learn the /paintblack, /paintred, /paintblue, and /paintyellow emotes.
Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Decadent Decoration

Description:
A single, unidentified memory of the lost.

Resistance rank required for appraisal: 15
Potential memories contained: Pure Essence of the Duelist, Lost Rend Armor
Name: Forgotten Fragment of Contention

Description:
A single, unidentified memory of the lost.

Resistance rank required for appraisal: 15
Potential memories contained: Pure Essence of the Fiendhunter, Lost Dervish
Name: Forgotten Fragment of Finesse

Description:
A single, unidentified memory of the lost.

Resistance rank required for appraisal: 15
Potential memories contained: Pure Essence of the Indomitable, Lost Aethershield
Name: Forgotten Fragment of Fortitude

Description:
A single, unidentified memory of the lost.

Resistance rank required for appraisal: 15
Potential memories contained: Pure Essence of the Divine, Lost Seraph Strike
Name: Forgotten Fragment of Divinity

Singular: copy of Modern Aesthetics - Early to Rise
Plural: copies of Modern Aesthetics - Early to Rise
Description: The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for weaving a simple-yet-elegant braid that can be employed by even those who are not yet fully awake. Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician. Unavailable to female Hrothgar.
Name: Modern Aesthetics - Early to Rise

Description: The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this limited edition of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques on transforming yourself into the prominent─some would say too prominent─member of the Scions of the Seventh Dawn, Alphinaud Leveilleur. Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician. Unavailable to female Hrothgar.
Name: Modern Aesthetics - Sharlayan Studies

Description: For some reason, ringing this bell summons forth a behatted and begloved embodiment of festive cheer. With that in mind, it would be rather a shame not to ring it.
Name: Snowman Bell

Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near the Lunar Whale will grant you access to its voluminous belly, which is not nearly as awful as it may sound.
Name: Lunar Whale Identification Key

Description: Raising this enigmatic gem aloft will summon forth a miniaturized version of the progenitor of all sin eaters, which may or may not be a good idea...
Name: Eden Crystal

Description: This horn-carved instrument emits an ominous tone that calls forth a hellacious, three-headed beast.
Name: Cerberus Horn

Description: This whistle emits a shrill tone that is said to summon a big shell, and presumably some sort of creature inside said shell.
Name: Big Shell Whistle

Description: This undeniably divine horn emits a rumbling tone that calls a six-legged steed to your side. Any nearby farriers will be rubbing their hands with glee at the profits they stand to make.
Name: Arion Horn

Description: This horn-carved instrument emits an ethereal tone that beckons a gwiber clad in emerald scale from its refuge.
Name: Emerald Gwiber Trumpet

Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your prototype roader will bring it flailing and thrashing to life.
Name: Prototype Roader Identification Key

Description: This whistle emits a slightly saccharine tone that is said to summon a creature that defies description, other than the fact it is mostly comprised of chocolate.
Name: Chocorpokkur Whistle

Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your Gabriel Mark III will bring it to life.
Name: Gabriel Mark III Identification Key

Description:
Few wavekin have ever been the object of so much anticipation, only to be followed by such crushing disappointment.

Use item to acquire the much-coveted Mora minion.
Name: Much-coveted Mora

Description:
Unlike the craft on which it is modeled, it will break immediately upon coming into contact with water.

Use item to acquire the Syldrion-class insubmersible minion.
Name: Syldrion-class Insubmersible

Description:
Those who think the hammer is just for show had best watch their toes.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Gaia minion.
Name: Wind-up Gaia

Description:
Try not to break it.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Palom minion.
Name: Wind-up Palom

Description:
The rosy cheeks and pronounced eyelashes indicate that this is the female half of a matching pair.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Porom minion.
Name: Wind-up Porom

Description: Based on one of the few people who had the chance to be a prince and a ninja, which seems like too much fun to squeeze into one lifetime. Use item to acquire the wind-up Edge minion.
Name: Wind-up Edge

Description:
Not to be confused with a sprig of broccoli.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Rydia minion.
Name: Wind-up Rydia

Description:
Based on the central corner of a one-sided love triangle, if such a thing is possible.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Rosa minion.
Name: Wind-up Rosa

Description:
For every person who has ever dreamed of owning a wheeled, spindly legged, trumpet-blowing mammet, there is this wheeled, spindly legged, trumpet-blowing mammet.

Use item to acquire the Save the Princess minion.
Name: Save the Princess

Description:
With a will to wander the world, one wonders whether said world will welcome this well-meaning watery whelp.

Use item to acquire the Drippy minion.
Name: Drippy

Description:
Very affectionate, but be prepared to make a quick sidestep if it comes running to greet you.

Use item to acquire the Trike minion.
Name: Trike

Description:
Remember: all that glitters is not gold. Sometimes, it is a beaver.

Use item to acquire the golden beaver minion.
Name: Golden Beaver

Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Gives the impression that one's head is large, orange, and bulbous, which may be an improvement in some cases.
Name: Magicked Prism (Bomb Head)

Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Causes a large “O” to appear in midair. Or is that an “O”?
Name: Magicked Prism (Numeral 0)

Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Causes a large “1” to appear in midair.
Name: Magicked Prism (Numeral 1)

Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Causes a large “2” to appear in midair.
Name: Magicked Prism (Numeral 2)

Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Causes a large “3” to appear in midair.
Name: Magicked Prism (Numeral 3)

Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Causes a large “4” to appear in midair.
Name: Magicked Prism (Numeral 4)

Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Causes a large “5” to appear in midair.
Name: Magicked Prism (Numeral 5)

Description:
A banded chest containing a full set of mirage gear.

Required level: 70. IL: 400. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.
Name: Mirage Gear Coffer (IL 400)

Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a potent healing technique.

※Only for use by blue mages.
Name: Whalaqee Angel's Snack Totem

Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a defensive technique.

※Only for use by blue mages.
Name: Whalaqee Dragon Force Totem

Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a long-ranged offensive technique.

※Only for use by blue mages.
Name: Whalaqee Matra Magic Totem

Description: An ornamented piece of parchment recognizing services rendered to this year's bugyo.
Name: Heavensturn of the Tiger Ticket

Description: A painting of the New Nest based off your own observations.
Name: Painting of the New Nest

Description: A painting of Featherfall based off your own observations.
Name: Painting of Featherfall

Description: A painting of the Risensong Quarter based off your own observations.
Name: Painting of the Risensong Quarter

Description: A painting of the Firmament based off your own observations.
Name: Painting of the Firmament

Singular: suit of ornate exarchic mail of maiming
Plural: suits of ornate exarchic mail of maiming
Name: Ornate Exarchic Mail of Maiming

Description:
To Eorzeans, the name may seem rather exotic, but the fish itself is as plain as can be.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Zagas Khaal

Description:
Though it may be named for the deftness with which it uses its claws as tools to methodically dismantle its prey, perhaps “butcher crab” would be a more fitting appellation.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Goldsmith Crab

Description:
Given the exacting standards of the skybuilders, the artisanal grade 4 variety of this species is anything but common.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Common Bitterling

Description:
The ability to fly puts the skyloach rather higher in the hierarchy of wavekin than its water-bound brethren.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Skyloach

Description:
Despite being an entity of unknown origin and possessed of mysterious powers, it nevertheless has a habit of getting caught on fishers' hooks.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Glacier Core

Description:
Its kissing days are over.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Kissing Fish

Description:
While this catfish may─according to the rumors─be able to split a horse in two, perhaps the ability to cut through a fisher's line would have proved more useful.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Cavalry Catfish

Description:
Only when the manasail dips below its usual high altitude does it find itself within range of a fisher's line. This probably explains why they do not do it more often.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Manasail

Description:
In the grand scheme of things, perhaps a flying mollusk is not so strange after all.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Starflower

Description:
It is common for creatures to be named for their color, but since “blue crab” was already taken, this species was granted somewhat more fanciful nomenclature.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Cyan Crab

Description:
It seems the skybuilders seek this particular variety of snake for its deadly venom. Exactly why they require deadly venom is a question best left unanswered, but it is clandestine plots such as these that keep food tasters in work.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Fickle Krait

Description:
These ferocious wavekin have a tendency to scare away more desirable fish. As such, the skybuilders seek to thin their numbers, preferably to zero.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Proto-hropken

Description:
While some wavekin are able to change their color to blend in with their surroundings, the ghost faerie takes this one step further by being almost entirely transparent. In a cruel twist of fate, this also makes it almost impossible for them to find a mate, which goes some way to explaining their scarcity.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Ghost Faerie

Description:
When it was first discovered, the ghostly coloration of this species led many to believe it was a waterborne ashkin. It was some time before anyone plucked up the courage to actually try eating one.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Ashfish

Description: While it may not be a horse, it is white, so at least that part of its name is accurate. ※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Whitehorse

Description:
Before it was first caught, fishers believed it to be a cloud drifting under the water's surface, despite the fact that would be next to impossible.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Ocean Cloud

Description:
This wavekin's dark coloration serves as camouflage in the ocean depths, but the effect is lost if it ventures into shallower waters. There is also the fact that its internal organs will rupture due to the changes in water pressure, as if any further discouragement were needed.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Black Fanfish

Description:
The legends speak of the sunfish aiding those stranded at sea to shore by letting them ride on its back. The skybuilders have decided to return the favor by catching and eating it.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Sunfish

Description:
Said to have been created from the beads of sweat that gathered on the Dawn Father and Dusk Mother's foreheads, the unfortunate name has made these delicious little fish rather difficult to sell.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Sweatfish

Description:
The sculptor's sawlike rostrum is often placed next to the meat of the fish for identification purposes at market.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Sculptor

Description:
Though this wavekin is unaware that it was named after the beast of legend, it certainly seems to relish playing the part.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Little Thalaos

Description:
Like its brethren the storm chaser, this fish uses gas expelled from its rectum as a crude means of propulsion. As its name would suggest, it spends much of its time chasing lightning bolts, though with little success due to the ludicrously slow pace at which it moves.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Lightning Chaser

Description:
The heavily armored protrusions that extend from what is presumably its head seem to be entirely at odds with the fact its innards are completely exposed. Some might consider this species to be an evolutionary dead end, yet it continues to survive to this day.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Marrella

Description:
Experts believe its enormous dorsal fin is used to repel creatures that enter its territory. This is also the part that often gets caught on a fisher's hook, so perhaps it is more of a hindrance than a help.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Crimson Namitaro

Description:
One would be forgiven for assuming the skybuilders were only joking when they requested a griffin be brought to them. Unfortunately─and inexplicably─they were deadly serious.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Griffin

Description:
Practically anything with “mega” in its name is bound to be big, and this overgrown dragonfly is no exception.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Meganeura

Description:
To Eorzeans, the name may seem rather exotic, but the fish itself is as plain as can be.

※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Approved Grade 4 Skybuilders' Zagas Khaal

※Not included in the fish guide.

Description: Processed silver beech lumber.
Name: Silver Beech Lumber

Description: An ingot of smelted duraluminum.
Name: Duraluminum Ingot

Description: A large block of solid crystal, ready to be chiseled into whatever form the craftsman desires.
Name: Solstice Ingot

Description: Finely woven cloth dyed a vibrant orange with gardenia fruit, rather than the expensive spice after which the color was named.
Name: Saffron Cloth

Description: A large piece of cured thylacoleo skin.
Name: Thylacoleo Leather

Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.
Name: Grade 4 Strength Alkahest

Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.
Name: Grade 4 Dexterity Alkahest

Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.
Name: Grade 4 Vitality Alkahest

Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.
Name: Grade 4 Intelligence Alkahest

Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.
Name: Grade 4 Mind Alkahest

Description: A robust grass resembling a horse's tail, often used as an abrasive.
Name: Horsetail

Description: A sizable piece of rock containing traces of the metal aluminum.
Name: Aluminum Ore

Description: This all-in-one abrasive, created for craftsmen of all disciplines─and even some with no discipline whatsoever─can be used to both sand metals and polish them to a lustrous sheen.
Name: Workbench Refining Sand

Description: Originating in the Far East, the fruit may be dried and used to dye cloth.
Name: Gardenia Fruit

Description: The hide of the thylacoleo─a primitive beastkin predator.
Name: Thylacoleo Skin

Description: The condensed aether of a once-living being. The essence of its essence, so to speak.
Name: Spirit Extract

Description: A rough-cut log of silver beech timber.
Name: Silver Beech Log

Description: A semi-translucent rock containing the rare mineral dolomite.
Name: Dolomite

Description: A mysterious crystal of purest white.
Name: Solstice Stone

Description: The cotton produced by this particular species is said to be as delicate to the touch as a raindrop. Unfortunately, this makes it rather difficult to pick without crushing the boll.
Name: Raindrop Cotton Boll

Description: Though this bark has a number of uses, being in an apparently semi-fossilized state does make it somewhat troublesome to work with.
Name: Wattle Petribark

Description: To the layman, hard water may sound like a convoluted way to say “ice,” but experts would disagree. In any case, it is at least soft enough to be poured into and out of a bottle.
Name: Hard Water

Description: The loathsome memory of a departed soul, forever trapped in crystal.
Name: Loathsome Memory of the Dying

Description: The haunting memory of a departed soul, forever trapped in crystal.
Name: Haunting Memory of the Dying

Description: The vexatious memory of a departed soul, forever trapped in crystal.
Name: Vexatious Memory of the Dying

Description: The delicate carving on this ancient artifact belies its pre-excavation position amidst so much midden.
Name: Timeworn Artifact

Description: A compound whose primary ingredient, aetherial siltstone, was said to have been used to fashion crystal foci in ancient Bozja.
Name: Aetherial Sealant

Description: A commissioned painting which depicts the Starlight Celebration choir and their delighted audience. It is so authentic that snow was used instead of white paint, although this soon melted, revealing the white canvas below.
Name: Authentic Choir Concert Advertisement

Description: Two cream-filled sponge cakes complete with strawberries on top. While it may not be the most obvious choice for a festive treat, the color scheme certainly conjures up images of the Starlight Celebration. The authenticity extends to the cream inside, which contains actual snow, although this does dilute the flavor somewhat. ※Cannot be retrieved once used. ※Can be used up to 10 times. Meal benefits when used: Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 10) VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12) Gear Durability Bonus: +3 EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)
Name: Authentic Starlight Roll Cake

Description: A stuffed goobbue sits within a festive wreath, its mouth agape, ready to devour your soul. It is so authentic that the makers claim it is made from genuine goobbue pieces, although it is probably best not to dwell on exactly what that entails.
Name: Authentic Starlight Goobbue Wreath

Description: A traditional Heavensturn decoration meant to beckon fortune through its depiction of a traditional bumper crop of rice, traditionally infested by mice. In addition to the stuffed mouse included, it also attracts living mice, which some may find to be a nuisance, but it nevertheless adds to the overall authenticity of the piece.
Name: Authentic Heavensturn Bounty

Description: Complete with a range of fruit and other sweet treats. Just try not to get any chocolate on the upholstery. While the creators claim that the parts pertaining to the fountain itself are entirely authentic, they make no such claims regarding the chocolate, which raises concerns as to what it actually is. ※Cannot be retrieved once used. ※Can be used up to 10 times. Meal benefits when used: Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10) VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12) Gear Durability Bonus: +3 EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)
Name: Authentic Chocolate Fountain

Description: The festivities never need come to an end with this stage adorned with peach blossoms. While the exterior is considered to be entirely authentic, the same cannot be said for the interior, but as the saying goes, “It's what's on the outside that counts.”
Name: Authentic Eastern Stage

Description: A princess needs no crown when this banner exists to always remind them how special they are. The feelings of undeniable specialness are─according to the makers, at least─rather authentic.
Name: Authentic Little Ladies' Day Banner

Description: This rabbit looks as if he walked straight out of a storybook, and is prepared to keep on walking. (Please contact authorities immediately in the event that the toy actually demonstrates ambulatory capabilities.) Although the makers claim it to be extremely authentic, when it comes to stuffed animals, perhaps the less authentic, the better.
Name: Authentic Stuffed Rabbit

Description: A cheerful hand-painted notice proclaiming the eggcellence of Hatching-tide. The feelings of guilt one eggsperiences when making egg-based puns in the vicinity of this poster are eggstremely authentic.
Name: Authentic Hatching-tide Advertisement

Description:
Though widely disparaged as fool's gold, there are certain obsessive miners who would trade sacks of genuine precious metal for this glorious hunk of iron and sulphur.

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Pyrite

Description:
“If you can't recognize the beauty inherent in its orthorhombic crystal system, then we can't be friends.”

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Chalcocite

Description:
Artistic collectors will swoon over the lustrous ochre pigment that can be produced from this seemingly unremarkable rock of iron ore.

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Limonite

Singular: bottle of rarefied Abalathian spring water
Plural: bottles of rarefied Abalathian spring water
Description: Vanu shamans collect spring water to make the paste they apply to their beaks before rituals. Some Vanu shamans are very, very particular about their spring water. ※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Abalathian Spring Water

Singular: handful of rarefied aurum regis sand
Plural: handfuls of rarefied aurum regis sand
Description: When the aether of one's opus must flow unimpeded, one cannot skimp on the conductive component of one's ink. ※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Aurum Regis Sand

Description:
The potential value of this uncut stone is obvious to the practiced eye. Especially if you love yellow.

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Raw Triphane

Description:
Rubies are red. Sapphires are blue. Star spinels are more of a violet, though, and that's the hue glinting from within this promising stone.

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Raw Star Spinel

Description:
“If I can cut this just so, it will provide the perfect accent for a rather rakish turban I've been weaving...”

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Raw Kyanite

Description:
Be sure to don your swimming trunks before losing yourself in the deep, deep blue of this entrancing raw gemstone.

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Raw Azurite

Description:
“It's beautiful! Stunning! Magnificent! Now find me three more.”

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Silvergrace Ore

Description:
Never has titanium and copper existed in a more harmonious blend of minerals. It promises to make a wonderful teapot.

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Titancopper Ore

Description:
One day, this unfinished gemstone of clearest blue could grace an elegant ring or an exquisite necklace or a face-smashing fist weapon. Possibilities!

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Raw Lazurite

Description:
Not quite clear and not quite white, you're not quite sure why the jewel hiding in this rock is so valuable.

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Raw Petalite

Description: “Don't you dare throw that over your shoulder. Here, use the table salt.” ※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Sea Salt

Description:
They say reef rock has been procured for restoration projects in a certain snowbound city. Perhaps this perfectly porous piece is destined for a structure of “holey” importance.

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Reef Rock

Description:
Even in its rough, natural form, the shimmering blackness of this jewel is almost dangerously captivating. So...pretty...

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Raw Onyx

Description:
A truly precious find for one invested in the finest facets of tungsten-based fabrication.

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Tungsten Ore

Singular: pinch of rarefied Gyr Abanian alumen
Plural: pinches of rarefied Gyr Abanian alumen
Description: “Well, tan my hide! You must have spent weeks in the mountains of Eastern Aldenard looking for this stuff.” ※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Gyr Abanian Alumen

Description:
Unconfirmed rumors tell of an eccentric Lalafell with plans to use these glowing grains to build a private beach. She'll probably need a few more handfuls...

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Mythrite Sand

Singular: bottle of rarefied Gyr Abanian mineral water
Plural: bottles of rarefied Gyr Abanian mineral water
Description: Should probably be saved for the concoction of valuable reisui, but it does make for a tasty cup of buckwheat tea. ※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Gyr Abanian Mineral Water

Description:
If this mineral was any aether-richer, it would have to pay taxes.

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Bluespirit Ore

Description:
The customer requesting this liquid-like sand was oddly specific about the number of grains in the handful.

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Manasilver Sand

Singular: pot of rarefied dark chestnut sap
Plural: pots of rarefied dark chestnut sap
Description:
Rather than experiment with amusing applications for this superior sticky substance, it's perhaps best to relinquish it to a tree sap professional.

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Dark Chestnut Sap

Description:
Gazing upon this rough-cut log, you cannot help but wonder if its lustrous lumber is destined for a valiant knight's lance or a bilge-bottomed buccaneer's bar stool. Anyone's guess, really.

※For collectable submissions only.
Name: Rarefied Dark Chestnut Log

Description:
